headline.main: For Kansas--From Lake Superior--Canal Agents Interfering in the Elections.

docs.lead_paragraph: A party of one hundred and twenty-five emigrants from New-England for Kansas want up the Lake last night. They take with them six engines from Rochester, and some patent grist mills from this city. All the party were in good health and spirits. The Lake Superior Journal of Saturday last, says the mining prospects are flourishing. The shipments since Aug. 12 amounted to over 275 tons copper, and 408 tons iron ore.
